reviews: We had an amazing experience at the hotel and meeting place. The food was delicious and the staff's attention to detail was incredible. Alejandro at reception and Paulo with our luggage were especially helpful. Our team appreciated the attentive service provided by the meeting room staff (our angels), including Virginie and Johanne who facilitated our events seamlessly. We highly recommend this venue. Just a small note, responses may require a bit of patience.

Novotel Les Halles is a fantastic mid-range hotel located just north of the Seine river in Paris. The truly multi-lingual staff was helpful, friendly, and efficient from the reception desk to the housekeeping team. My room was spotless when I arrived with a cool view of the interior courtyard. The hotel was within an easy walk to many cafes, shops, and marvelous landmarks. I made the 15-20 minute every day to La Cuisine Paris on the Rue de Rivoli and past the Hotel de Vill, and it was wonderful. The breakfast layout every morning was impressive and fresh and the coffee (and to go cups) was plentiful. I plan on returning to Paris in the next year, and I 100% will stay here again (and again and again!).

Frankly, you are better off staying in a Airbnb in the same area. Services are poor. We had to lug our luggage to the room from the car (group included senior citizens), one room had no running hot water for last 2 days. Getting another room for a shower before we headed to the airport was not a pleasant experience. On the way back we we asked specifically the night before if we will get porters to help with bags in the morning. Answer was no. In the morning, lo and behold, there was someone. We had to push for help on this. We were all quite upset by that time. Left with a funny feeling - would this happened if we were not Indians.

Overall, choose an Airbnb in the area if possible. The location is good.

My granddaughter and I met in Paris for a long weekend and completely enjoyed our stay at Novotel Paris Les Halles. Its location is perfect -- steps away from a Metro stop for easy access from the airports and easy walking distance to the Louvre, Notre Dame, Sainte Chapelle, and other treats. The reception staff was friendly and efficient, especially with accomodating our arrival and departure times. The rooms were charming and tres comfy, and the neighborhood full of charming cafes if we wanted to branch out from the hotel for meals. Tres bien all around.

Stayed here for three nights with my wife and daughter over February half term. Hotel is well situated next to the Les Halles train station which has very easy links to the whole of the Metro system across Paris. The room itself was quite small given we had booked this for three people. My daughter had a separate rollup bed which was placed in between the double bed and the window. This meant that there was not much space to move around the room at all.

The room was generally clean with a decent bathroom shower sink and toilet although again this was on the small side. Our main gripe with the room was the air-conditioning/heating which was way too hot and couldn’t be adjusted. We had two engineers to the room at different times, the second engineer managed to get it to a reasonable temperature, but it was still too hot.

As regards the rest of the hotel, the service at the reception desk was poor in respect that we had explained the air conditioning issue to one of the receptionists who was going to fix the matter whilst we were out. Unfortunately, he went off duty, and we had to explain the whole position again later in the day.

There was quite a wide choice at breakfast, although we experienced queues during the busy February half term week when we came down to be seated at around 9:30 am. The restaurant itself was quite cold, which matched the atmosphere in the bar which was in a large soulless open space.

Overall, the hotel was satisfactory, just, based on its location, hygiene and food quality.

Even for a hotel chain, the standards here are amazing. The rooms are spotless and spacious. The staff is super friendly and helpful, and the location is second to none located directly across from Chatelet station. Notre Dame is only a five minute walk and the Louvre can be found with a very short ride on the M1 Metro. I will not be staying anywhere else when I come back to Paris.

Perfect Location as you can walk to sights like theNotre Dame, the Louvres Museum and Pompidou Centre. Rivoli Street is in 50meters. Visitors can walk the area of Marais and find many cafe and restaurants to choose from. The Hotel etrance is next to the elevator of Chattelet Les Halles train station where Metro, RER A and B comes through, very convenient for visitors travelling on plane or are planning to Visit Disneyland.
The hotel room was very clean and comfortable wwith nice view.From my window I was able to see the Basilique du Sacré-Cœur.
When you book this hotel dont forget to include breakfast. It has a large variety to choose from everything were delicious and the price seems to be a bargain as kid have breakfast for free.

All the hotel staff where very friendly and helpful provide an Excellent service to me and my family. Especially the guy from Portugal (Sorry forgot his name) felt him as my friend.
I conclusion my experience in that hotel was Excellent. Definitely it is not a cheap hotel but in Paris where everything is so overpriced the location the breakfast and the friendly hotel staff make it a value for money Hotel.

I stayed her with my Mum and Sister for 3 nights and it was wonderful.
The hotel was extremely clean with lovely modern décor throughout.
Staff were very attentive, especially the young woman in Guest Relations. I also have to speak highly of reception, we arrived the day before the first transport strikes and were made aware of this and all they could do to help, due to this it didn’t hinder our plans to much.
The bedrooms were extremely comfy and soundproof, our room looked out the back over the shopping centre etc but we didn’t hear a peep.
The hotel is in easy walking distance of the Louvre and Notre Dame, as well as plenty shops, cafes and restaurants.
East to get to and from airport, as well as Disney on the RER (just not on strike days haha).
I would absolutely stay here again and highly recommend the Novotel Les Halles.

Location middle of everywhee, right on top of the metro.
This is what we paid for. Location

Breakfast: just okay. - wished for better for the price.

Cleanliness: good
Front dest: although they are busy, still trying to accomodate. Carine was superb. She helped me sincerely. Really appreciate what she did

Value for money 3/5.
As i have stayed at other hotels in Paris, i would rather stay at a hotel located not so center with lower prices (as long as still close to subways)

Room size: expectedly not large, just like other super big cities. But my superior room provided a sofa, i used it to place my big luggage

Staff helpful and friendly. Rooms lovely and clean. Location was ideal for us. Walking distance to Louvre, Opera House and Hop on Hop off Bus etc. Close to a main shopping street and plenty of cafes and restaurants. Train station right outside. We would definitely stay here again

The hotel is pretty good with an amazing location and accessibility. It is just outside metro which takes you directly to airport or Disneyland. Secondly louvre is walking distance. The big bus hop on hop off stop is walking distance. Shopping malls - both luxury and regular are nearby. A lot of food joints.

The rooms are small but that is typical of Paris. Breakfast was ok by European standards. The staff is polite and helpful

This hotel has superior service, top to bottom. The staff was always friendly and helpful with every question or concern. Two employees, Lucille and Carl, went above and beyond with exceptional service to my family. They both are found working as check-in specialists, but offered excellent concierge services when needed. I highly recommend this hotel for your stay.

Everything is very good, Perfect location, room/bathroom very confortable, good cleaning, excellent hospitality. Price a little hight and internet could be faster. Definately would come back. I’ve been already three times.

I was in the hotel for working reason
Good experiece
High price for the service offers in the room.
No kit for travelers
Very good the reception service in particular pablo that takes care of our luggage

we love the hotel, the accommodations and the hospitality, especially from Mr. Paul and Mr Guy. we also liked the accessibility to the metro and the main stores, meaning the hotel is in a great location.

It Wash everything perfect
It is the second time in this hotel, the localization is very very good
O Hope return soon
Tks to MS Luca she was so simpatic
The brackefest is vert very good
See you in the next paris

Excellent location, very close to Chatelet metro station. Our 2 rooms had a very decent size. We also enjoyed the breakfast. Look for Paulo (reception clerk) and he will provide you lots of local hints and tips.

We stayed for three nights, the hotel Is very well organised, we did the on line check in and out and in five minutes we got the keys of our room. Executive room with Queen size and sofà for two teens was nice and comfortable. Excellent breakfast available . We could leave our luggage at the hotel so to visit Paris last time few hours before Flight departure. It was Amazing holiday with my family!

Spent 3 nights here on a trip to celebrate my parents 45th wedding anniversary.
The staff on the front desk were very friendly, especially Manuel Alejandro.
Unfortunately, the standard rooms are very basic and all the rooms on the first floor only have one internal window. Our room was very basic and certainly not what I would consider 4 star.
However, we didn’t spend much time in the room and so this didn’t impact our stay.
The breakfast area is too small for the number of guests and as such there was a short wait every morning. Breakfast was ok - not a great selection, but what was there was fresh and of decent quality.
On the plus side:
Great location - Châtelet metro station is right outside the hotel and so using public transport is super easy.
Nice staff - front desk and bar staff.
Communal areas of the hotel are good - big lobby, nice bar etc.

Excellent bedding. Fantastic toiletries and cleaners. Very good variety of food and very tasty and exquisite. The reception was amazing and receptionists were very attentive and organized when it came to what we needed. Nice and kind staff, we especially liked Paulo, he was extremely nice with us and amazing at his job. He offered us many services which we are extremely grateful for, Paulo was great to us.

Novotel Le Halles Paris Hotel will is a Wonderful Hotel! The hotel is lovely, friendly staff and extremely helpful, central location close to many places to visit , restaurants, and shopping.
Definitely recommend!!!

Only one night here, in a very beautiful place!
Paulo help us with everything, he become one of our in few minutes! Very appreciated.
The breakfast is very good prepared, nothing missing. We will be back !

The location is perfect. There is a metro station right in front of the hotel and a lot of restaurant options. Easy walk to most of the places to visit in Paris. Staff is helpful starting from the checkin. Rooms are clean and at a decent size for Paris.

I was walking around Paris and was over stimulated due to a concussion. In my search for a quiet spot with good chairs I found the Novotel. I was welcomed by Paulo and he helped met settle down in a quiet place where I could de stimulate. He checked up on me to see if I was doing well and even ordered me a cup of tea. Fantastic service in a time of need.

Hanged a "Do Not Disturb" Sign on the door during my whole stay. Tried to ask for the staff to take out the garbage and refill the tea bag when I am inside the room for 6 times and not succeeded. Then, someone came inside and cleaned up the garbage when I am out even though the sign was still hanging. Since the tea bags were not refilled, I tried to request the cleaning staff in the corridor to do me a favour and they sneered and said ok. Finally, of course no tea bags were refilled. It seems the cleaning department is weird. Don't know why these simple and normal request cannot be taken care. Never experience this in other hotels.

Great for family, fantastic location, Musee Louvre only a couple of blocks. Can walk everywhere, many bars cafes and restaurants (oh and Westfield) on your door step. Hotel needs a little fine tuning in terms of room amenities, breakfast staff are lovely and the buffet is varied but not spectacular.

One of the best meals i’ve ever eaten. Amazing service by everyone but especially Tom who was very friendly and welcoming. He also went the extra mile and recommended us where to visit in Paris. Would definitely dine here again and I would definitely recommend.

Fantaatic hotel,clean,best service(have to mention Paolo who helped us with everything we needed).
Big rooms for Paris.
Perfect location,next to the metro&forum des halles.
Big big thanks to Lilian ( amazing Lilian) who helped us with the booking.( we were a group of 17 people and she arranged it perfectly).
We will be back

Paulo in the lobby was a huge help! He’s amazing and goes above and beyond! The hotel was beautiful. They had a cotton candy station set up when we went in. The bar is quite large and open as well. Everyone there has excellent customer service.

The hotel experience was fantastic especially one of the members of staff Paulo who was always more than willing to help us and advise us on how to make our visit to Paris as thrilling as possible! A big thank you to Novotel and specifically Paulo! We would definitely come back again!

I will spare my words in this review because our hotel choice for our three-day stay in Paris couldn't have been better. The hotel is excellent with spotlessly clean facilities, spacious rooms, delicious breakfast, and professional staff who really acknowledge what politeness and service mean. It is located right in the best spot in a vibrant area with lots of cosy bistros and restaurants around and a shopping mall right next to it, which prompts no worries for noisy issues or unsafety, though. The metro station is literally 50 metres away to get everywhere around Paris. What else could a family with two 12-aged children ask for?

Great location! You need to remember the exit number when you take the metro as it’s just next to the Hotel entrance but you could exit in different directions because it’s a huge connection station.

The room is quiet with street view. The front desk is very helpful!

Great service at both the hotel and restaurant ! Staff was so friendly and accommodating. Close to lots of great places. Not far from the airport either. Highly recommend visiting when coming to Paris!

We specifically selected this hotel for the Novotel reputation, location, and equally important, air conditioning in the room considering that in Europe this can be hard to come by.

The website, app, and every document related to this hotel reservation indicated A/C would be available.

Upon checking in, the rooms(we had two) were incredibly hot. We let AC run while at dinner and came back to discover no change.

Upon inquiring the hotel informed us that the AC is only available in Summer months(we were there mid-April). We had simply been running ambient air thru the fan. We asked to move rooms and were accommodated and new rooms were marginally better. All of this happened at 11PM.

We were told to keep the windows open but with young kids this was not an option as the windows are low enough for them to easily fall out.

We all slept poorly. B/c we were only in Paris for 3x days it was not worth moving hotels despite looking into it. I inquired the following morning with the manager regarding a refund/discount because we were not receiving accommodation that was advertised. We were offered free breakfast and for them to put fans in our rooms to see if it would help.

Unfortunately the fans were inadequate and very loud making sleeping with them on unacceptable.

The following day upon returning mid afternoon for a nap, the rooms were exceptionally warm. Again I inquired with a diff manager and this time I was offered "$80 in Accor credit and free breakfast". This was unacceptable. I explained that we had booked two rooms at an exceptional cost based on completely inaccurate advertising and that more needed to be refunded. I was advised the manager from the second day would get in touch which they never did. This is why I've ranked them a 3. They were all accommodating but there was never any follow up. We were there for a very short stay and I wasn't wasting more time discussing this with them at the hotel after already having done one move and one in person discussion with the morning manager.

At this point, I decided it would be easier to deal with them through my CC company and dispute the stay. When I reached out to Novotel corporate they simply forwarded the dispute to the hotel.

For info, the staff at the hotel was always trying to be accommodating and I appreciate that, but what we got was not what was advertised and that is what I am upset with.

While a relatively good location near transport, there were lots of vagrants in the general vicinity of the hotel that left us feeling unsafe walking in the area at night.

Reception service was excellent, room size and quality was good. My Sister and I only had breakfast (not able to select Family above). We only had breakfast which was mediocre. Anyhow, a good, short experience.

Novotel Paris Les Halles is an exceptional hotel that offers an unforgettable experience. The rooms are spacious, modern, and impeccably clean. The location is unbeatable, with easy access to public transportation and a multitude of restaurants and shops nearby. The staff is friendly, attentive, and always ready to assist. Highly recommended!

A great location!
Comfortable rooms. Bigger than what you usually find in central Paris.
Metro station right outside the hotel.
Very rich breakfast!
Dinner was amazing. Special tasty food and best service by Tom, our waiter.
We will definitely be back!

Perfectly located in the heart of Paris, close to everything and with a metro station just in front of the hotel. Rooms are comfortable, large enough and very quiet, but htat is standard in hotels in this category.
The BIG plus of this specific hotels is the extra ordinary friendly staff. We stayed 8 nights here and already on the second day the staff treated us like good old friends. At the reception we were always greeted with a big smile, even if we were just passing by. At the breakfast (excellent!) we were served with that extra friendliness which makes the difference.
Thank you, Novotel Les Halles, for choosing such great people to work for you.

It was amazing and Eloise was fantastic ! La bulle was amazing too! Thank you for this moment. I will comme back for sure! I work all day and i like the bar! I recommande it Of course. Lunch bar and space are amazing

We stayed here 4 nights.
Strengths- Good location, surrounded by shopping malls/ restaurants with metro very close by.
-Staff at the reception is very courteous and helpful.

Weaknesses- No value for money!
Some of the rooms sold under “ executive rooms” are frankly budget hotel type rooms. We were put in one such initially until we complained since we paid equivalent of AUD 670/night!! The second upgraded room was reasonable which was also “ executive” room according to the staff! So be careful when booking and check what room you are getting.
No glasses in the rooms. We were given paper glasses in the first room!No milk to make tea. Hotel did not have firm pillow which I had requested. Nothing gets delivered to the room. You just have to go and get it from reception/ restaurant etc.
overall 4 star hotel but very cost conscious and run like a budget hotel. Don’t expect any 4 star comforts.
Stay somewhere else if you can find other option for same price.

We had a great time here at Novotel Paris Les Halles we can recommend it for everyone who stays in Paris, because of its very good location and the kind and helpful staff, especially Mahmoud and Luca whom we talked more with. Merci beaucoup!

The stay at Novotel Paris Les Halles was brilliant. The hotel is right in the centre of the city and everything is easily accessible. In particular, staff member Paulo was fantastic and really helped with my luggage.

I can only guess that room 208 is positioned above the kitchen. Staff turned up from 4.45am and could clearly be heard shouting, singing along to the radio and generally banging about! Reported it to Reception then checked out shortly after 6am. Not recommended for a good night's sleep.

Paulo was excellent. All the Staff was very nice. Good and clean rooms. Breakfast with tasty and healthy food. Excelent location, near to the train and metro. This hotel is very pleasant for family trip.

While the hotel has a nice lobby the 4 star label stops there. The rooms are a decent size but are badly set up. If you happen to go to the bathroom at night whomever is in the room with you will get a blast of light in there face and hear everything as the doors are closet style and the "wall" to the room from the bathroom is a shower door.

Gym is small and doesn't have many weights mainly 3 or 4 cardio machines.

Breakfast is not worth it, cross the street and hit the bakery or the small restaurant at the corner.

Customer service is terrible, never have I gone to a 4 star hotel where nothing is their fault and the customer is wrong . Check your bill before you leave and your credit card statement after. You may be surprised at what is charged after you check out.

I stayed with a big chain thinking that service and brand would be upheld, I was wrong with this one. Look elsewhere and pay extra if needed.

A big shout out to Mr. D (with a slight limp - sorry I forgot your name). He was very helpful.

I would rate the hotel 4.5 stars. half star taken away for not having a proper drop off point. Because this was 10 day business trip to France, I had a lot of bags in the taxi, which I had to wheel and carry from the road to the hotel.

I had minimal contact with the staff because I was out at 8am and back at midnight everyday, but each time I had a question or needed help, they were quick and happy to help.

Location-wise was fantastic. Metro station just outside, which I used for work. Lots of eateries nearby.

I will stay here again the next time I return to Paris.

Excellent location, walking distance from
different restaurants, metro station and shopping malls. Juan help us to arrange transportation and tours information. He was always helpful, responsive and friendly even when we hsven’t asked for anything

My wife and I went to Paris for the first time in March 2023 and we could not have picked a better place to stay than Novotel Paris Les Halles. The location is perfect, the metro which is very easy to use is located less than a minute walk from the hotel. We were able to get everywhere we wanted on the metro. The hotel was wonderful, the staff was very friendly and extremely helpful. I truly felt like a valued guest during my stay. Our room was very luxurious. The bed was comfortable, the room was very spacious with a great view. Many, many choices of restaurants within walking distance plenty of shops close to the hotel. This was a wonderful vacation, We will definitely stay at Novotel Paris Les Halles again when we come back to Paris, a great value, great service we could not ask for more.

Located in the center of Paris. Not easy to reach by taxi, tell your taxi to reach the hotel for the Rue des Bourdonnais. The staff was amazing, very helpful, I got an upgrade to a nice suite, the room was very functional, mini bar is free (except alcohol). Plenty of nice restaurants in the neighborhood. I was really surprised by the breakfast, simple but super smart, with some juicers to make vegetables juice, a machine to make peanut butter, coffee machines but also some coffee in some pots for those who like americano, excellent hot chocolate in pots and therefore you avoid long queue at the coffee machine.

New hotel in the best location in Paris and safe, the rooms are relatively big to Paris and have almost everything that is needed for the stay, there is a minibar in the room but I would preferred to have a refrigerator, the hotel is well managed and clean the service was great, the hotel is close to all attractions, lots of restaurants and bars in the area, Metro station almost in the hotel, shopping center just behind the hotel and lots of other stores, overall very satisfied

Everything was great!
From the first moment at the reception we got a warm welcome, very professional and friendly staff.
The room was very clean and comfortable with coffee machine and a capsule every day.
Love this hospitality.
The location is perfect right on Shatlet metro station, plenty of great restaurants and patisserie.

Excellent location, polite and well-trained staff - especially Paulo - modern and clean accommodation, restaurant with a wide menu and breakfast that exceeded expectations. Would go back and recommend.

Our one-week stay was excellent. English-speaking staff is friendly and helpful. Beds are comfortable. The shower is strong with plenty of hot water. Room was warm and quiet. The location is fantastic. The hotel is located next to the entrance to the Metro and the RER train, so it is very easy to reach from the airport and Gare du Nord. There are many excellent restaurants nearby on Rue Montorguiel and shopping in Forum les Halles. The hotel is within walking distance of Saint Chappelle and the Pompidou Center. We would happy to stay there again!

Had a wonderful time Luia was very helpful. She made a few recommendations on what to do and the best Metro route to get there. She also recommended L Escargot Monte for dinner which was within walking distance. The food was very good. The hotel is in a great location, close to the metro and the staff is very helpful.

A long weekend in Paris with wife and brother-in-law. We took an executive suite which was a good size for three adults and would suit families too. Helpful pre-advice after email question on travelling into the very busy and complex Chatelet metro/RER station from Eurostar. (Blue RER line and head for Exit 1) All the staff were very willing and great service, comp drinks on arrival, juices and canapés comped to the room and comped mini bar fridge for those taking a suite (check beforehand, maybe some of this is for loyalty prog members which I am). Free gym. Breakfasts OK - no problem if you are hungry - it's all there. Room warm when Paris was very cold. Quiet.

On the final day happily stored our luggage so we could be out and about before going home. Reception quickly solved a hitch with the shower in our room. Alejandraud in particular was great in Reception - but in truth everyone was. You could say the hotel was a little 'soulless' but it's clean, modern and it works and looks out for its guests - you are made to feel you matter and they try.

I spent a wonderful long weekend in Paris. Staying at the Novotel Paris Les Halles was the best choice I could have made 🙂
Wonderful and very friendly staff, great location, and in the evening a beautiful, spacious room to come back to.
The hotel is within walking distance from the Louvre, Notre Dame, ... and two metro/RER stations are close by, so also the rest of Paris is within easy reach.
In summary: thank you Novotel Paris Les Halles for making my stay so very enjoyable!

Great stay particularly enjoyed the guys at the desk who were very welcoming and in particular Paulo the concierge was a great help, resourceful, friendly and always had a smile on his face. Highly recommend
The location of this hotel was fantastic. The staff was very helpful since we weren't very good at speaking French. The grounds were very clean. Would definitely stay here again Highly recommend.

The location is unbeatable - just outside of the underground/station with the direct train to the Airports and all around the city. The rooms are of decent size and clean. The reception is efficient at both check-in and checkout. The Wi-Fi is decent. Zero plastic for disposable use throughout the hotel is appreciated.

There some things that this hotel could improve: the room temperature was very high and the controller did not seem to be working; the breakfast is rather poor in selection of plant-based options e.g., yoghurt, pastry, etc., the pastry is not to French standards which is a shame for a French hotel chain; the beds and pillows were rather too soft or too hard; the room amenities for a 4-star hotel were missing body lotion, decent hand soap, etc.; the TV was not working at all; the safe box was blocking all the time so we gave up on it; the noise from other rooms could be heard in our room. Overall value for money is rather poor.

Took my daughter for her first visit,
Brilliant location, brilliant staff team.
Immaculately clean.
Will definitely be back.
Everything about the stay was made so simple.
Any requested was supported immediately.

We stayed at the hotel and this was our first dinner in Paris. The service was very very nice and the food was very good. We had the risotto and the beaf with baby potatoes. Very nice all together!!!!!

First class Hotel. Decor pleasing, staff superb, safe environment as you need your room key to work the lift. Breakfast was absolutely delicious and the choice was amazing. You can even make your own fresh smoothie if you want!! Hotel room was comfortable and very clean, even the sofa bed was comfortable. We had two travellers in the group who suffer terribly with their backs and they slept comfortably. Fantastic location! 8 min walk down the street to the louvre past the most wonderful patisseries. Near the big Paris bus hop on, which I would highly recommend, aswell as the saine river cruise just behind the louvre. I would recommend getting the no4 metro from the gare du nord if arriving by eurostar. It will save you 60 euros as taxis overcharge. The metros very clean so are the streets come to think of it. When I return I will definitely stay at this hotel!! You do have to pay 150 euros deposit when you arrive and they will deduct a tax from it at the end. It's not a lot. Its only a few euros each.

a really good hotel, very very good atention!! thanks to jonathan for the love and understanding he gave us during our stay. Very tasty breakfast and very comfortable room, all facilities very clean and well maintained

Nice attencion!! Good breakfast and experiencie, the personal is very lovely and they will help you for whatever you needs. Don’t loose the oportunity of come here and enjoy a really big and good city like Paris is. Thanks to Jonathan for help me with all!!

I really enjoyed the experience. The breakfast is great the rooms where cozy and quiet and the staff was very friendly and helpful specially Jonathan and Paulo who helped us decide where to go and advised us the best restaurants. Thanks to this hotel this was one of the best travel experiences I have ever had.

The Novotel Les Halles had everything our family needed for a lovely 8 night stay in Paris: comfortable rooms and beds, a great central location, great breakfast, a nice lounge and lobby, a great restaurant (loved the truffle Risotto), and wonderful staff. Olivier at the front desk and Barbara at the bar/restaurant went far above and beyond to help us and honestly everyone at the hotel was just helpful and friendly.

The location in Central Paris meant that we could easily walk to a lot of destinations, including tons of great nearby shops, restaurants, and even our tour pickup spot; and having the entrance to the Chatelet station a few steps from the hotel entrance meant that we could easily get to and from all the places we couldn’t walk to. This was especially valuable when returning late at night from Disneyland on the RER.

I had heard some negative things about the area and the Chatelet station in particular. Yes, the station is a bit of a labyrinth because so many lines stop there, but it’s easy enough to navigate if you just follow the signs, and the RAPT app really helps plan your routes… I much prefer this to having less access. We did not have any issues from a safety standpoint either. The hotel is kind of tucked away from the busier parts of the neighborhood, and for the most part the area was just filled with people out enjoying themselves. The neighborhood was a huge plus as far as we were concerned since there is so much close by.

We didn’t really have much of a view from our room (we overlooked the Forum), but everything else about our stay was wonderful!

Tip: the later you go to breakfast, the busier it gets; much calmer in the first couple of hours.

I’m not good at speaking english well. But he was very kind and provided good service. I could keep my luguages at the front. he was very kind. Thank for his service and he made me good memory in Paris.

Very well placed on the center of Paris this hotel brought us a very pleasant experience, modern, well decorated, and with amazing breakfasts and dinners. The staff was also very friendly. Regarding the staff my special thanks to Paulo who promptly gave us tips for visiting Paris and who made us feel at home. Likewise Jonathan also received us very well, helped us with hour lauggages and was very friendly in general. Great choice of hotel, for anyone visiting Paris. Joao

We stayed at Novotel Les Halles for 3 nights, excellent location, 1 minute walk from a very well-connected central train and metro station, Chatelete station. Big spacious rooms. Really friendly and courteous staff, especially Olivier and Luca. Quick response from the reception, made our stay very comfortable.

Stayed here with work and without a doubt a great location with lovely friendly and helpful staff. Would highly recommend this as a hotel to stay in for anyone in search of a hotel. This will not disappoint!

Excellent experiance! Large and comfort superior room. A delicious breakfast with many choices. Just outside the hotel there is the main station that most of metro lines interchange but also the railway. Access by walking to many sites like Museum du Louvre and others.

First, Prime location - very close to Rue de Rivoli, Louvre, and Pompidou Ctr. Metro is just outside the hotel, together with a big shopping center.
Very clean, welcoming&helpful staff, very good breakfast, spacious rooms and much more.

Perfect location, great room (suite) and pleasant staff.
We enjoyed it very much, and would definitely pick this hotel again when we come back to Paris.
The staff was also very attentive and welcoming. Big shout out to Mahmoud.

This was the first time me and my partner visited Paris, and we could not have asked for more from the hotel staff. From the first moment we arrived, the staff were welcoming and helped with our luggage. When we checked in, the gent (who’s name we regretfully didnt get but we do recall him informing us he was from Lebanon) was really nice and made the time to talk with ourselves to make us feel welcome. The gent made sure to speak through everything with us and any questions we had were answered. He was extremely attentive, and himself plus the other staff members are some of the best we have come across in holiday stays.
The room was lovely and the location of the hotel is superb. The rooms were cleaned everyday which we appreciated, and all facilities accessible.
When we come back to Paris, we will definitely be staying here again.
Thankyou for making our first time in Paris as welcoming as possible.

Impressed by the hotel’s actions on sustainability - full set of full sized toiletries to use, leftovers from buffet breakfast given to the needy, room access card, welcome water containers all contribute to less plastic usage. Location is very central - can walk to most sights. Staff are all very helpful and most speak English. Their welcome drinks include non- alcohol drinks which is more welcoming to all. Highly recommend this Hotel, it is already popular that thisvis the first hotel we had to queue to get into our breakfast

My mom, daughter (14) and I stayed at Novotel Paris Les Halles the week before Christmas and had a wonderful experience! Everyone was extremely helpful during our 5 night stay. Rooms were clean, very modern and comfortable. The location was awesome as well. There were two stand out employees who went above and beyond: Karl and Adrien. Both helped us anytime we had questions, needed a taxi or even when we check out, helped store our luggage and then gather it when we came back from lunch. I would highly recommend staying at this location!

Location, facilities and the amazing Staff!
Many thanks to Benjamin and Jonathan!
Always choise #1 for me when traveling to Paris
I do recommand all to visit Novotel Les Hales. Fos single, couple and family events.

Dan

The hotel has a good breakfast. Rooms are clean. Bathroom is ok. However, this is a VERY noisy place. Rooms are noisy and you can hear your neighbors often, even if they are only talking. (Our neighbors alarm clock would wake up my entire family on the other room.) The location is also very noisy. Windows are not soundproof and there was a different turmoil outside every night, either people singing, screaming or fighting. Hard to have a good night’s sleep. Do not recommend, particularly if tou are traveling with children.

The location of the hotel its great! Paulo works there and he was very helpful ! He speaks portuguese and he could understand us.
The hotel is clean and the Forum des alles is in front, with a lot of stores, restaurants and metro.
Paris is amusing

Cozy Novotel les halles, great location, metro practically at the door, attentive staff, especially Paulo, kind and giving us tips in general, no difficulty checking in or any other need, we were taken care of in everything

Our stay was wonderful! The rooms were very large, especially for Europe. The staff was incredibly hospitable, helpful and professional! The location is very central, close to a metro station, close to great shops, bakeries and restaurants. I would stay here again!

My husband and I had a wonderful experience at this hotel. The breakfast buffet was delicious and had an excellent varied selection of different items. The staff were very accommodating and friendly as well. We had originally experienced issues with accessing wifi in our original room. We hardly could connect to the wifi because of the location this room. Djamel at the front desk, was able to help us find a different room that had much better wifi signal and a lovely view of the city. Thanks so much for your help!!

Aside from the hotel experience, the location is perfect. Right out the door is an entrance to access the RER and Metro if you wanted to get around the city or outside of it to explore. But even without that, there are plenty of great sites to see all within walking distance (Louvre, Sainte-Chapelle, Notre Dame, etc). Just a few steps further from the hotel you'll find a myriad of amazing restaurants to try. We spent a good chunk of time just wandering through the rows of tasty looking restaurants trying to decide where to eat every time. If you're looking to shop, Rue Saint-Honore is a great place to explore flagship stores of some famous French brands (and a very easy walk). There is also a Westfield right in front of the hotel as well if you want something even closer!

We thoroughly enjoyed our time in Paris and would definitely recommend this hotel to our friends and family in the future. We hope to be back another time :)

Great Location. Few steps from the huge train and metro station.
Few steps from a Shopping mall.
Nice rooms and great breakfast with lot of options. I strongly recommend to chose breakfast included up front.
Staff very friendly. Paulo at the door was very helpful.

The hotel is well located , Clean with helpful staff.
Staff speak lots of languages for easy communication for non French speakers.
Paulo was extremely helpful and friendly.
Had helpful tips on where to eat. Treated everyone with a friendly smile and wildlings ness to help made a fantastic impression from check in to check out

We had the best time! The staff was friendly and attentive and the hotel location is just perfect! Walking distance to attractions such as George Pompidou, Norte Dame, Rue de Rivoli and Louvre. Besides that, the metro station Les Halles is one of the main one, so lots of lines stop at it, including the one to CDG. The restaurants, Boulangeries and Creperies surrounding the hotel are all great!

Great service amazing location we really enjoyed our stay.
We visited the hotel January 2023 and it was our second time staying here. The location is superb, you can walk anywhere. Shopping center is nearby and so is the metro. Service was great

Stayed 3 nights from 6-9 January at Novotel Les Halles!
The location is very good, one step to Chatelet subway and can see the subway from my room, walking distance to Opera/Louvre Museum, and alot of cafe and restaurant surrounding hotel area.
Its is recimmended for tourist!

My fave room is #554

this property always fullybooked since arrived 3 days ago and get upgraded 1 level up to Executive Room, free 2 bottle water n voucher welcome drink.
free bfast for weekend and varieties of food not much.

special thanks to Front Desk Kariba who helped me moved to other room 🙂

We spent two night at Novetel Paris Les Halles, experinced a good stay. The team was very helpful and warm ; especially the staff Adrien Bamba.

When we were going from Paris to London, Adrien Bamba first helped us contact the Taxi driver; after evaluating the traffic conditions and time, he recommended us to use public transportation. Adrien Bamba was off work when we leaving, and he saw us were not familiar with the subway routes in Paris, then explained the route to us and brought us to the station. He was very enthusiastic to guide us, and finally we took the train to London smoothly.

We were very pleased and satisfied with the service and the efforts that Novetel Paris Les Halles had put in.Definitely will coming back at Novetel Paris Les Halles in future.

The Novotel really lived up to expectations - it's a lovely hotel in a very convenient location (eg, you can comfortably walk to Notre Dame and the Latin Quarter) and most importantly, has a metro station outside its front door (essential in Paris!). We were upgraded to Exec Rooms with 2 Queen Beds in each room, which was fantastic for the 6 adults in our party - the rooms are particularly generous in size for Paris.

I haven't been to Paris for a long time and one of the stand-outs for us was the customer-oriented nature of all staff we interacted with --- it made the stay so pleasant and enjoyable. In particular, (and I'm sorry for the mispelling), but Damiel (I think it's pronounced Jamal) was just really so welcoming when we checked-in and in subsequent conversations - it's funny how one person can really enhance a stay at a hotel!

Best location next to all transportation in middle of the city
Great breakfast
Big clean rooms
Very kind staff
Housekeeping every day
There is a delicious restaurant in the hotel with a nice sitting place in the yard

We arrived late (after 2 days in Disney) and were checked in by a lovely member of staff. The room was spacious, had a mini bar and lovely Juliette balcony. Delighted as this was our first time in Paris. We had a drink in the bar that night. Staff were attentive. The breakfast was amazing, excellent choice of hot and cold, make your own juice bar, kids section, the sausages were lovely. We didn't eat dinner as we found a great place within a 5min walk. The hotel was within walking distance to Louvre (8min). It has a shop next door and is opposite a boulangerie and donuteria (which were both delicious). The transport links are excellent with the Westfield on your doorstep. Check-out was so efficient. Staff were so friendly. We left our luggage while we went out for the day. We weren't sure how to use public transport for getting to CDG but Paulo was outstanding. So helpful, polite and friendly, a real asset to the company. We can't wait to return to this hotel!

Fantastic hotel in an unbeatable location. We have been treated exquisitely. The treatment we received from Paulo was outstanding. It is a pleasure to travel and meet professionals like him. Thank you very much!

The hotel was brilliant and situated in a vibrant neighborhood, and the metro was practically at your doorstep. The station provides easy access to every area of the city thanks to the availability of both the metro and RER. There are a lot of cafes, bakeries, and restaurants nearby. The Seine, the Louvre, La Samaritaine, and many other attractions were all within walking distance of the hotel.

The staff was friendly and spoke excellent English, and the room conditions were well-maintained. Great!

Was really impressed with Djamel and Paulo when we first arrived as they offered good recommendations and fixed our airport transfer with little to no hassle. The room was a little warm but it was quite luxurious with modern fittings. Also, it was very conveniently located near the metro and mall! Would definitely recommend heading down to the breakfast restaurant early, and do approach Paulo if you have queries about where to eat or go in Paris!

Novotel Paris Les Halles is probably the worst four star ALL Accor hotel I've stayed in as Silver card member.
Customer service was non existent from the start of our stay until the end. Paris is a beautiful city but our room was 2nd floor with a view of a shopping mall. No help at front desk and a promise that 'management' would contact us.
Breakfast was a disappointing affair with questionable hygiene procedures in place.

Avoid this, allegedly, four star hotel and look elsewhere would be our strong advice to avoid a disappointing experience.

We had the best experience here. Everything was of good quality. The staff was very friendly and helpful and the rooms were comfortable and clean. The room had an iron and blow dryer, the breakfast was comprehensive. The hotel stores you luggage if you arrive earlier than 14:00 or leave later than 11:00 and Karl was very helpful.

We have had a very nice stay in Novotel Les Halles, the best accommodation we've had during our 10 day trip in Europe (we had four). Location is the best since the train station is literally just outside the hotel. Breakfast was really good too and had so much to choose from. Their bar offers free croissants and pain au chocolat. The room amenities were very impressive - from the lighting, bed, showers. Too bad we only stayed for one night.

All of the hotel staff were very accommodating as well, especially Karl 🙂

Very well placed hotel, lovely staff (we particularly liked Paulo who sorted our luggage on check out) great room, delicious breakfast (mini muffins are amazing). We would definitely stay here again!

Sole negative was the bathroom, which although very cool with the transparent to frosted glass, woke up the whole room if you got up to go to the loo in the night. Beautiful, but not very practical.

The hotel was wonderful, generous hospitality. They provide full service, and high level security. I recommend all Israelis to come there. There is an employee there named Paolo who speaks Hebrew and is super nice to Israelis. highly recommend. There is a huge mall near the hotel + close to 5 minutes to the Louvre.

We stayed at the Novotel Hotel, Les Halles.
One staff member was exceptional, Paolo. This was surprising as most staff at reception were quite cold and not welcoming.
He helped with booking a taxi and helped us with our luggage. He even took our photo by the Christmas tree in reception.
A true star and credit to the hotel who spoke several languages.

Mr R Phian
